Refactors Amsterdam cruises data structure for consistency
Standardizes the format of cruise details, improving readability and maintainability.
Updates location data and itinerary descriptions to ensure uniformity across multiple cruise entries, enhancing clarity for future developers.
Addresses inconsistencies in object notation and enhances the organization of cruise information.

Refactors testimonial data structure for consistency
Updates the testimonial data format to use consistent object syntax across all entries.
This change enhances readability and maintainability of the code, ensuring a uniform structure for future updates.
No functional changes were made to the testimonial content itself.

Refactors Amsterdam Amstel Chophouse menu structure
Updates the menu data structure for the Amsterdam Amstel Chophouse to use consistent object notation for properties.
This change enhances readability and maintainability of the menu items by standardizing the format across all categories and items.
No functional changes are introduced, but it improves the codebase for future enhancements.

Removes redundant crew member entries for Amsterdam team
Streamlines the crew member list by removing outdated and redundant entries from the Amsterdam team.
This change enhances maintainability and clarity of the codebase, ensuring only relevant team members are included.
Fix syntax errors by adding missing commas in various scripts

Adds new cruise itineraries and updates existing details
Introduces several new cruise itineraries departing from Amsterdam, enhancing the diversity of options available to travelers.
Updates include improved descriptions, adjustments to pricing, and detailed itineraries with time at sea and on land.
Additionally, introduces new contact personnel for the cruises, ensuring better customer support and engagement.
These changes aim to provide a richer experience for users and attract a wider audience to the cruise offerings.

Adds new testimonials for Amstel Chophouse and Canal Farm Table
Introduces a comprehensive set of testimonials for Amstel Chophouse and Canal Farm Table, enhancing the dining experience narrative for users.
Removes outdated testimonials for Amsterdam Bar & Kitchen, Amsterdam Brasserie, Amsterdam House, and Anne Frank Saloon to streamline content.
Improves user engagement by providing fresh, appealing reviews that reflect current offerings and guest experiences.

Adds Atlantic Charcuterie menu and removes Atlantic Room menu
Introduces a comprehensive menu for the Atlantic Charcuterie, featuring various categories and detailed item descriptions, enhancing the dining experience.
Removes the existing Atlantic Room menu to streamline offerings and focus on the new charcuterie concept.

Removes obsolete menu data for Boston restaurants
Deletes menu data files for Beacon Smokehouse and Boston Chophouse, streamlining the project by eliminating outdated content. This change helps maintain an up-to-date and relevant codebase for restaurant menus.

Updates menu items and descriptions for Bermuda restaurant
Refines the menu structure by updating item names, prices, and descriptions to enhance clarity and appeal.
Replaces old dishes with new ones that reflect modern culinary trends while maintaining a focus on quality and local ingredients.
Improves the overall dining experience by offering a more diverse and enticing menu selection.

Adds menu data for Alexanderplatz Atelier; removes Bavarian Pizzeria menu
Introduces a new menu data structure for the Alexanderplatz Atelier, showcasing a diverse selection of dishes and drinks, while enhancing customer experience with detailed item descriptions and dietary information.
Removes the existing Bavarian Pizzeria menu to streamline offerings and focus on the new dining experience.

Adds new restaurant menu data for Barcelona locations
Introduces comprehensive menu data for two Barcelona restaurants, Barcelona Ramen-Ya and Barri Gòtic Barbecue.
This addition enhances the culinary offerings available in the application, providing detailed descriptions, pricing, and dietary information for each dish, thereby improving user experience and enabling better dining choices.
No related issues or tickets.

Adds Blue Fine Dining menu and removes Blue Harvest menu
Introduces a comprehensive menu for Blue Fine Dining in Bangkok, featuring a diverse selection of dishes across multiple categories.
Removes the outdated Blue Harvest menu to streamline offerings and enhance user experience.

Adds menu data for Blue Atelier and removes Blue Barbecue
Introduces a new menu for the Blue Atelier restaurant, featuring a comprehensive selection of dishes across multiple categories, enhancing the dining experience with detailed descriptions and dietary information.
Removes the previous Blue Barbecue menu, streamlining the restaurant offerings to focus on the Blue Atelier's culinary theme.
This change ensures a more cohesive menu presentation and aligns with the current dining strategy.

Removes Auckland cafe and provisions menu files
Deletes the Auckland cafe and provisions menu files to streamline codebase and remove outdated or redundant data.
This change enhances maintainability by eliminating unused components, allowing for a more efficient and cleaner project structure.

Adds new menu data for Blue Project in Athens
Introduces a comprehensive menu for the Blue Project restaurant in Athens, replacing the previous Ristorante menu. This update enhances the dining experience by offering a diverse selection of Italian-inspired dishes across various categories, including main courses, appetizers, desserts, and drinks, to cater to a wider range of preferences and dietary requirements.

Adds Amstel Chophouse menu data for Amsterdam
Introduces a comprehensive menu data set for Amstel Chophouse, featuring detailed descriptions, categories, and items, enhancing the restaurant's offerings for customer engagement.
Removes the outdated Amsterdam Bar & Kitchen menu data to streamline the codebase and focus on current menu options.
This update improves the culinary representation of the restaurant and provides a richer dining experience.

Updates Amsterdam team members with new roles and bios
Replaces existing crew member data with updated entries for the Amsterdam team, enhancing diversity and reflecting current staffing.
Adds new members with detailed roles, experiences, and language proficiencies to improve the team's representation and operational capabilities.
Removes outdated entries to maintain relevance and accuracy in crew member information.

Refactors file deletion scripts for improved organization
Consolidates and reorganizes the deletion scripts for crew members and restaurant menu files into a more coherent structure.
Removes redundant scripts and unifies the logic to streamline operations, enhancing maintainability and clarity.
Additionally, updates import paths and improves user interaction for file deletions, promoting a better user experience.
Fixes #123
Add geographic data for additional cities and their coordinates

Enhance transportation services by adding new aircraft, vehicles, and yachts to the selection guide. Updated aircraft options include Cessna Citation M2, Cirrus Vision SF50, Gulfstream G280, and more. Expanded vehicle offerings feature luxury models like Bentley Flying Spur, Rolls-Royce Cullinan, and armored vehicles. Introduced new yacht options such as Celestial Legacy and Quantum Blue, along with detailed amenities and features for each category.

Add detailed FAQs addressing group travel, sustainable practices, cultural immersion, family services, luggage transfers, dietary needs, and connectivity options to enhance user support and engagement.
Refactor contact department descriptions for clarity and engagement
Implement code changes to enhance functionality and improve performance
Add testimonials for aviation, general, ground transportation, homestay, and yacht services to enhance user engagement and showcase diverse client experiences.

Enhance cultural highlights for homestay destinations in India, Japan, Italy, Vietnam, Morocco, and Nepal with detailed activities and experiences, including subtitles for each location to enrich user engagement and provide a more immersive travel narrative.
Add FAQs for special occasions, loyalty rewards, language support, travel insurance, and property previews
Refactor homestay interfaces to improve structure and type safety
Add imports for TourCategory and react-icons to enhance tour category representation
Enhance tour category descriptions for improved clarity and engagement
Refactor homestay heritage locations to use HomestayHostLocations type for improved type safety
Adds Location type with detailed attributes for enhanced geographical context
Adds country information to homestay destinations for improved clarity and organization
Adds detailed host information for homestay locations in India, Japan, Italy, and Vietnam to enhance cultural immersion for guests
Adds new homestay locations in India, Japan, Italy, and Vietnam with detailed descriptions
Make buttons in PrivateAviation and YachtCharters components navigate to contact information
Replaces button with a clickable component to navigate to homestay destinations
Adds button to request transportation on the TransportationPage
Adds general testimonials data for enhanced user experience
Enhances HomePage layout with new sections for features, popular trails, and testimonials
Adds CityAttractions and BaseAttraction interfaces for attraction data structure
Removes YachtRoute interface and associated meeting point type from routes
Refactors TeamMember interface and renames TourGuide to ContactPersonnel, updating optional properties
Adds contact department information for customer support and inquiries
Adds new font files for improved typography
Refactors global styles and updates color variables for improved theming
Adds TeamMember and TourGuide interfaces for staff management
Adds YachtRoute interface for managing yacht route details
Adds Testimonial interface for managing user testimonials

Adds Tour interfaces and types for tour management
Introduces interfaces for TourCategory and BaseTour to streamline the management of tour-related data.
Enhances type safety and organization for tour attributes, including locations, images, and pricing details.
This foundational structure supports future development of tour services.

Adds utility functions for string formatting and accents removal
Implements several utility functions to enhance string manipulation capabilities, including converting camelCase and kebab-case to title case, formatting numbers as currency, creating URL-friendly slugs, and removing diacritical marks from strings.
These additions improve the handling of various string formats for better usability in applications.

Adds utility functions for filtering and sorting arrays
Implements new functions to filter arrays of objects by specified properties and sort arrays based on dates, prices, and durations.
Enhances the utility library by providing additional capabilities for handling common array operations, improving code reusability and efficiency.
These changes facilitate easier manipulation and organization of data structures throughout the application.

Adds function to generate random dates from next Monday
Implements a new utility function that generates an array of random dates starting from the next week's Monday.
This function allows users to specify the number of dates and an optional range in days, enhancing date manipulation capabilities for applications.
The generated dates are formatted as 'YYYY-MM-DD' strings, promoting consistent date handling across the application.
Adds displayRatingStars component for rendering star ratings based on a given score
Refactors StaffTeams type to use TeamMember; removes unused Testimonial type; adds MeetingPoint, Flags, Package, Details, Location, and ContactInfo types for enhanced data structure.

Refactors navigation imports and updates Footer and Header components for improved structure and styling; replaces NavBar with DockNavigation; enhances DynamicBreadcrumb with new icon and segment formatting.
Adds HeroSlantedPhotos component for displaying images with rotation effects
Adds Loading component for improved user experience during data fetching
Updates icon library to use react-icons and adds lh3.googleusercontent.com to remote image hosts for improved image handling
Adds Accordion and Calendar components, and Menubar implementation with various subcomponents for enhanced UI functionality and user experience

Refactors popular tours component for improved clarity
Removes unused imports and logs to streamline code readability.
Enhances filter handling by memoizing functions, reducing unnecessary re-renders.
Improves error logging specificity for better debugging and modifies city info retrieval logic for robustness.
Optimizes category sorting and ensures consistent handling of tour data.
Enhance meeting point details for Portland and Pucallpa tours with addresses, coordinates, instructions, and contact numbers for improved user guidance.

Enhance tour details for Berlin, Bhaktapur, and Blagaj
- Added new attributes to tours including popularity, adventure, cultural, culinary, spiritual, nightlife, wellness, luxury, and art/music indicators. - Updated meeting points with detailed addresses, coordinates, instructions, contact numbers, and emails for each tour. - Expanded FAQs for each tour to provide comprehensive information on accessibility, historical significance, culinary experiences, and local customs. - Improved descriptions of unique experiences and interactions with local culture, enhancing the overall tour offerings.
Refactor Beijing tour descriptions, pricing, and details for enhanced clarity and appeal; update images, meeting points, and FAQs for improved user experience.

Enhance Ayutthaya and Bali tour details with additional attributes, meeting points, and FAQs
- Added new attributes (isPopular, isAdventure, isCultural, etc.) to Ayutthaya tours for better categorization. - Updated meeting points in Ayutthaya tours to include detailed instructions, contact information, and coordinates. - Introduced comprehensive FAQs for each Ayutthaya tour to address common inquiries. - Enhanced Bali tours with new meeting points, FAQs, and additional tour options including Uluwatu Temple & Kecak Fire Dance and Ubud Monkey Forest & Rice Terrace Trekking. - Improved cancellation policies and inclusions/exclusions for clarity.

Enhance Atlanta and Atlas Mountains tours with detailed attributes and FAQs
- Added new attributes (isPopular, isAdventure, isCultural, etc.) to various tours in Atlanta and Atlas Mountains. - Included comprehensive meeting point details for each tour. - Expanded FAQs for multiple tours to provide better information on physical demands, accommodations, food, and cultural etiquette. - Updated cancellation policies and available dates for several tours.
Add meeting points and FAQs for Amsterdam and Anchorage tours; update images and tour details
Adds new attractions to Da Nang tour data, enhancing cultural and historical offerings

Refactors attraction and tour interfaces for clarity
Improves the structure of attraction and tour interfaces by introducing base interfaces and consolidating common properties.
This change enhances maintainability and readability, separating core attributes from specific flags and details.
Additionally, it standardizes the handling of shared properties, facilitating future expansions and modifications.
Update Da Nang tour details with new images, descriptions, and meeting points

Updates meeting point instructions to be required
Changes the meeting point's instructions property from optional to required.
This ensures that additional instructions are always provided for clarity in meeting arrangements.

Improves accent removal functionality in strings
Enhances the `removeAccents` function by adding specific replacements for characters "đ" and "Đ" before removing diacritical marks.
This ensures that accented characters are handled more accurately, improving string normalization.
Enhance city name processing by removing accents for tour data and attractions fetching

Updates import paths for tour categories
Refactors the import statements for tour categories to use the correct path, enhancing code organization and clarity.
No functional changes are introduced; this update improves maintainability.

Update import path for tourCategoryMap constants
Refactors the import statement for `tourCategoryMap` to point to the correct location in the `info` directory.
This change ensures that the application accesses the updated and accurate tour category constants, improving maintainability.
Add tour categories and mapping for quick lookup

Adds booking functionality and tour guide details
Implements a comprehensive booking interface for tours, including date selection and participant count.
Enhances the tour page by introducing features to fetch and display tour guides based on specialty, while presenting similar tours for user convenience.
Improves overall user experience with loading states and structured tour information display.
Remove meeting points from various tours in Anchorage, Athens, Atlanta, Atlas Mountains, Austin, and Bali; add popularity and other attributes to tours in Athens, Austin, Bali, and more.
Add detailed inclusions, exclusions, itineraries, highlights, and meeting points for Barcelona tours
Enhance meeting point details display with address, coordinates, instructions, and contact information
Update Tour interface to use MeetingPoint type for meetingPoint property
